comments.text: I have great respect for Prime Minister Narendra Modi especially for his discipline, honesty, maturity, and how he represents India on the global stage. But I can’t ignore the fact that India's core problems  like corruption, unemployment, and a failing justice system  still remain unsolved. And it makes me wonder... Is it possible that even someone like Modi is not fully in control anymore? Is the system so broken that his own team, or party, is not letting him act freely? After all, he's aged now, and maybe he’s being pressured or ignored from within  something we, the public, never get to see. So my honest question is: Can one honest leader really clean a corrupt system if the rest of the system is not ready to change? Or are we expecting too much from just one person?

शिक्षा स्वास्थ और insurance सबसे महंगा हो गया है। सारे देश की social welfare की schemes का बोझ middle class पर डाल दीया गया है। क्या मोदी अपने जेब से थोड़े ही पैसे बाट रहा है...?😮😢
